95
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,250
Yes, sir.

96
00:05:53,540 --> 00:05:54,300
Uh...

97
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,100
Yeah, I got a pen.

98
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:58,020
What are the names?

99
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:05,190
All right, so the names dad
gave us they're all couples?

100
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:07,350
Three different couples all went missing.

101
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:09,700
And they're all from different
towns, different states?

102
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:12,220
You must right. Yeah, Washington, New York, Colorado.

103
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:15,150
Each couple took a road trip cross-country.

104
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:16,800
None of them arrived
at their destination.

105
00:06:16,835 --> 00:06:18,250
None of them were ever
heard from again.

106
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:20,460
Well, it's a big country, Dean.
They could have disappeared anywhere.

107
00:06:20,470 --> 00:06:21,580
Yeah, they could have,

108
00:06:21,590 --> 00:06:24,180
but each one's route took them through the same part of Indiana...

109
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,640
always on the second week of april,

110
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:28,680
one year after another after another.

111
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,350
This is the second week of april.

112
00:06:30,510 --> 00:06:31,360
Yep.

113
00:06:31,590 --> 00:06:33,550
So dad is sending us to Indiana

114
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:36,800
