You know which god you're dealing with?

384
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:50,110
Nope, not yet.

385
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:52,590
You figure out what it is,
you can figure out a way to kill it.

386
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:55,640
I know. I'm actually on my way to a local community college.

387
00:23:55,675 --> 00:23:57,270
I got an appointment with a professor.

388
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:59,010
You know, since I don't have my

389
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:01,940
trusty sidekick geek boy
to do all the research.

390
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:04,980
You know,

391
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,720
if you're hinting you need my help,

392
00:24:07,210 --> 00:24:08,150
just ask.

393
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:10,320
I'm not hinting anything.

394
00:24:12,860 --> 00:24:13,760
Actually...

395
00:24:17,940 --> 00:24:19,270
I want you to know...

396
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,060
I mean, don't think...

397
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:23,790
Yeah,

398
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:25,150
I'm sorry, too.

399
00:24:28,390 --> 00:24:29,270
Sam...

400
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:31,600
you were right.

401
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:33,610
You got to do your own thing.

402
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:35,100
You got to live your own life.

403
00:24:36,060 --> 00:24:36,950
You're serious?

404
00:24:37,830 --> 00:24:39,210
You've always known what you want,

405
00:24:39,360 --> 00:24:40,570
and you go after it.

406
00:24:42,330 --> 00:24:43,570
You stand up to dad.

407
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:45,630
and you always have.

408
00:24:46,590 --> 00:24:47,700
Hell, I wish I...

409
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:51,750
anyway...

410
00:24:53,460 --> 00:24:54,860
I admire that about you.

411
00:24:56,340 --> 00:24:57,510
I'm proud of you, Sammy.

412
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:00,760
I don't even know what to say.

413
00:25:01,780 --> 00:25:03,380
Say you'll take care of yourself.

414
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:05,550
I will.

415
00:25:10,070 --> 00:25:11,380
Call me when you find dad.

416
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:13,490
Okay. Bye, Dean.

417
00:25:37,010 --> 00:25:38,010
Who was that?

418
00:25:43,030 --> 00:25:44,060
My brother.

419
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,220
What did he say?

420
00:25:49,020 --> 00:25:49,950
"Goodbye. "

421
00:25:53,100 --> 00:25:56,050
It's not every day I get a research question on pagan idolatry.

422
00:25:56,780 --> 00:25:58,190
Yeah, well, call it a hobby.

423
00:25:58,350 --> 00:26:00,310
But you said you were interested in local lore?

424
00:26:01,150 --> 00:26:03,900
I'm afraid Indiana isn't really known for its pagan worship.

425
00:26:04,310 --> 00:26:05,540
What if it was imported?

426
00:26:05,650 --> 00:26:07,690
You know, like the pilgrims brought their religion over.

427
00:26:07,850 --> 00:26:09,400
Wasn't a lot of this area settled by immigrants?

428
00:26:09,490 --> 00:26:10,080
Yeah. Mmm..

429
00:26:10,660 --> 00:26:12,350
Like that town near here, Burkitsville,

430
00:26:12,590 --> 00:26:13,710
where are their ancestors from?

431
00:26:13,830 --> 00:26:15,930
Northern Europe, I believe. Scandinavia.

432
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,720
What could you tell me about those pagan gods?

433
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:20,220
Well, there are hundreds of norse gods and goddesses.

434
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,840
I'm actually looking for one,

435
00:26:22,010 --> 00:26:23,200
might live in an orchard.

436
00:26:27,250 --> 00:26:28,520
A woods god.

437
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:30,170
Well, let's see.

438
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:38,050
Wait, wait, wait. What's that one?

439
00:26:39,740 --> 00:26:41,650
That's not a woods god, per se.

440
00:26:42,690 --> 00:26:43,900
The Vanir?

441
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:47,460
"Vanir were norse gods of protection and prosperity,"

442
00:26:47,495 --> 00:26:49,550
"keeping the local settlements safe from harm. "

443
00:26:50,430 --> 00:26:53,190
"Villages built effigies of the Vanir in their fields. "

444
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,650
"Other villages practiced human sacrifice,"

445
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,850
"one male and one female. "

446
00:26:59,350 --> 00:27:00,970
It kind of looks like a scarecrow, huh?

447
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:04,080
Well, I suppose.

448
00:27:05,150 --> 00:27:08,220
"This particular vanir, its energy sprung from a sacred tree"?

449
00:27:08,770 --> 00:27:12,110
Well, pagans believed all sorts of things
were infused with magic.

450
00:27:13,250 --> 00:27:15,740
So, what would happen if the sacred tree was torched?

451
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:17,820
Do you think it would kill the god?

452
00:27:19,580 --> 00:27:20,390
Son,

453
00:27:21,570 --> 00:27:23,660
these are just legends we're discussing here.

454
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:25,570
Oh, of course.

455
00:27:26,470 --> 00:27:27,440
Yeah, you're right.

456
00:27:29,420 --> 00:27:31,080
